      "acceptanceCriteria": "The model form must capture nonlinear contact between screw and rod, elasto-plastic material response of Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM F136, and large-displacement kinematics. Justification must reference published literature or prior FDA-accepted submissions demonstrating adequacy of the chosen constitutive and contact formulations for pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear contact (augmented Lagrangian), elasto-plastic Ti-6Al-4V material (bilinear isotropic hardening, E=114 GPa, σ_y=795 MPa per ASTM F136), and large-displacement formulation were employed. Model form selection is supported by Nagaraja et al. (2019) and prior FDA submissions. Achieved level 3 meets the required level."
